Don Bhai😡, chalo main bilkul beginner level se step by step samjhata hoon $ aur # ka concept Linux me. Ye aapko hamesha yaad rahega.

1️⃣ Terminal prompt kya hota hai?

Jab aap Linux me terminal kholte ho, top pe kuch likha hota hai, jise prompt kehte hain.

Example:

[kali@kali ~]$

Ye batata hai aap kaun ho, kaunse system pe ho, aur kaunse folder me ho.

2️⃣ $ ka matlab

$ ka matlab hai aap normal user ho.

Normal user = wo user jise system ke basic permissions hain.

Aap files create/delete kar sakte ho jo aapke folder me hain

Lekin system files (root ke folders) me changes nahi kar sakte

Example:

[kali@kali ~]$ pwd
/home/kali

Yahaan kali normal user hai

$ ka matlab hai limited permissions

3️⃣ # ka matlab

# ka matlab hai root user (superuser)

Root = system ka master user, jise sab permissions hain

Files delete kar sakta hai system me

Software install/uninstall kar sakta hai

System settings change kar sakta hai

Example:

[root@kali ~]# pwd
/home/kali

Yahaan root ka username hai

# ka matlab hai full power, sab kuch kar sakta hai

4️⃣ Regular vs Root
Symbol	User Type	Permissions Example
$	Regular user	Home folder me files edit kar sakta, system me nahi
#	Root / superuser	System ke sab files edit kar sakta, full control
5️⃣ Summary concept

$ → normal user → safe, limited permissions

# → root user → full control → careful use karo, galti se system break ho sakta hai

Terminal prompt ka symbol hamesha batata hai kaun sa user currently active hai


